    "summary": "H\u00fcseyin is a highly accomplished professional in impact investment, asset management, and finance, with extensive experience across various sectors with a specific focus on emerging country SMEs. As the co-founding CEO of BiD Capital Partners- impact investment advisory and management firm in the Sub-Saharan Africa and Benelux, he has played a pivotal role in driving the organization's initiatives. H\u00fcseyin serves as the GP/IC Chair of the Impact Mezzanine Fund investing in  Agri SMEs by a gender lens approach and holds significant positions such as the Vice Chair for the Rwanda Startup Fund and an Independent Member for the United Nations Capital Development Fund TA Project Committee. He is also actively involved as a Board Member at EBAN and represents Rwanda as a Senator at the World Business Angels Investment Forum (WBAF). Before his tenure at BiD CP, H\u00fcseyin established Angel Wings Ventures, a family office advisory firm, and gained valuable experience in investment and portfolio management with prestigious organizations such as Royal Dutch Shell Group, ING Bank, PYMWYMIC, and Amsterdam Park Capital Partners. H\u00fcseyin holds a BSc in American Studies from DEU and an MSc in Banking and Finance from the University of Stirling, UK. His diverse background, in-depth industry knowledge, and commitment to driving positive impact have positioned him as a respected thought leader and public speaker in the global impact space.\n\n 24+ years of multi-asset investment experience, 10+ years of commitment to Impact Investment and entrepreneurship, +15 years working and investing in emerging markets with a specific focus in Sub-Saharan Africa.\n\nCEO, CFO, CIO, Board Member. \n\nInvestment Fund and Portfolio Management. Family Office. Transaction Advisory. Transaction Facilitation. Program Management. Structured Finance. Treasury Management. PE- VC Advisor Manager. Impact Assessment. M&A Corporate Finance. \n\nBiD Capital Partners, PYMWYMIC, Shell, ING, AmsterdamPark Capital, and Angel Wings Ventures.",
